<subSubSection id="8F4A56401DFCF118EBC9C5F5E1BC0898" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A7458749DCE1C8278F4436EB42E332C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="67E0CD60236A89541ADEC4EE7096EB34" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall a much lighter-coloured species as in 
<taxonomicName id="8201CCB9A9DD9AA6D9114B05D8D86019" genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis id="5EC9109BA79834D0F0CA81755BC10D53" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a red-orange metasoma, and red-brown mesosoma and head, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="15CF52FE1ACDA099E0EC1AABCBF0111D" genus="A." lsidName="A. anyskop" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="anyskop">
<emphasis id="12F56E164B77078036FDC170F0A80362" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. anyskop</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0BDD137F8FB1B41E551E988BD6183AEA" genus="A." lsidName="A. robertsoni" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="robertsoni">
<emphasis id="EBB23AC0D6268893DCD25DFEC8409C10" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. robertsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a dark brown-black body, and 
<taxonomicName id="642164586675AA0947F8E603356DA131" genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis id="6FEE79065D9D9908779B3C1C5DAC39C3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an orange-yellow metasoma contrasting strongly with the darker head and mesosoma; 
<taxonomicName id="F1EE3579DFF34E129812C8F80B1538E7" genus="A." lsidName="A. obesa" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="obesa">
<emphasis id="713B31EC686E117A60E67066984252F2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. obesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has OOL shorter than LOL, whereas it is longer than LOL in 
<taxonomicName id="A189DBD65CD55B0FBCF5BF9E44452A1F" genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis id="B91CECF1386B151DA6F10B99DE4CBAC9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and equal in length to LOL in 
<taxonomicName id="EEB9B98BB370182CD4D3C1422C3EC6E8" genus="A." lsidName="A. anyskop" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="anyskop">
<emphasis id="C75D64FD0E4669B31E1EF425B0CB3EBB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. anyskop</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0C5A43071EB11B2773362C142752F71F" genus="A." lsidName="A. robertsoni" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="robertsoni">
<emphasis id="2160FA4AE630548A13624CB05036191F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. robertsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; notauli are broader, 3
<normalizedToken id="28F330EB404EF8C4845023C9C1F96C16" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide as in 
<taxonomicName id="3CEEE13A45F5AF89B0B35FF316E6994F" genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis id="B272614D2D817C761FB9E7A3EA40B8CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas remaining species have narrower notauli, at least 5
<normalizedToken id="BF450275A0F8CA7A922DF4D20F3647EC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; mesocutum polished between notauli as in 
<taxonomicName id="DC3030BBDDF162E2FB9C8634E672588D" genus="A." lsidName="A. robertsoni" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="robertsoni">
<emphasis id="BD1C0EA0F15250CA9C9547B6D0955DB1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. robertsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, alutaceous reticulate in 
<taxonomicName id="99A41DF2629135FE29B2066FC1867749" genus="A." lsidName="A. anyskop" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="anyskop">
<emphasis id="DD75DFEE0629754E3956AD7638A10A6D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. anyskop</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="642C5E4669DDF3274AD4284672CA0F31" genus="A." lsidName="A. quagga" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="quagga">
<emphasis id="9C7481DCA892B34231B6B1D204504AEC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">A. quagga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; only a single strong dorsal striation on mesopleuron, whereas other species have two or more striations.
</paragraph>
